'''Futuribles International''' (formerly '''Association Internationale Futuribles''') is a [[Paris]]-based international, independent, private non-profit organization network on [[future studies]]. It was created in 1960 by [[Bertrand de Jouvenel]] while the "Centre d’études prospectives" was created by [[Gaston Berger]] in 1957.

The organization main focus is on the impact of [[Information technology|new technologies]], [[social policy|social policies]], [[Lifestyle (sociology)|lifestyle changes]], [[strategic foresight]], and the emergence of an [[information society]].

