{{taxobox | image = Harryplax severus, male paratype dorsal.jpg | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | subphylum = [[Crustacean|Crustacea]] | ordo = [[Decapoda]] | infraordo = [[Crab|Brachyura]] | familia = [[Christmaplacidae]] | genus = '''''Harryplax''''' | genus_authority = Mendoza & Ng, 2017 | type_species = '''''Harryplax severus''''' |type_species_authority=Mendoza & Ng, 2017 }}
'''''Harryplax''''' is a genus of [[crab]] containing the sole species '''''Harryplax severus''''', native to Guam, where it is found in offshore coral rubble. Measuring {{convert|7.9|by|5.6|mm|in|abbr=on}}, ''H. severus'' occurs at depths of {{convert|1|to|7.6|m|ft|abbr=on}}. First collected in 1998 and described in 2017, the genus name honors collector Harry T. Conley, as well as the literary character [[Harry Potter (character)|Harry Potter]], an allusion to Conley's "uncanny ability to collect rare and interesting creatures as if by magic." The species name alludes to [[Severus Snape]], also from the ''Harry Potter'' series.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mendoza|first1=Jose C.E.|last2=Ng|first2=Peter K.L.|title=''Harryplax severus'', a new genus and species of an unusual coral rubble-inhabiting crab from Guam (Crustacea, Brachyura, Christmaplacidae)|journal=ZooKeys|date=2017|volume=647|pages=23–35|doi=10.3897/zookeys.647.11455}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Greshko|first1=Michael|title=Pale, Beady-Eyed Crab Named for Harry Potter|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2017/01/new-crab-species-harry-potter-characters-severus/|website=National Geographic News|date=23 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Geggel|first1=Laura|title=Accio Crab! Newfound Crab Honors Harry Potter and Professor Snape|url=http://www.livescience.com/57601-newfound-crab-named-for-harry-potter.html|website=Live Science|date=23 January 2017}}</ref>
